tput CHEBI:233617 ! terreate`.\n+- `creation_date` and `term_tracker_item` were left unchanged.\n+- The overall logical structure and parentage were left intact.\n+\n+Rationale\n+\n+- The issue discussion converged on keeping the GO term labels in the biologist-friendly `terreic acid` form, while retaining the pH 7.3 ChEBI form (`terreate`) in the logical definition, consistent with GO chemical-entity practice.\n+- The follow-up request explicitly asked to swap the primary name/synonym and to fix `PomBase:vw` to `GOC:vw`.\n+\n+Validation\n+\n+- Checked current term stanzas in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` before editing.\n+- Used the standard GO checkout/checkin workflow with local term files.\n+- Ran `make travis_build` in `src/ontology` successfully.\n+\n+Checklist\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context reviewed and request clarified from comments\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: current ontology validated as part of `make travis_build`\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: existing terms and related precedents checked with `obo-grep.pl`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: reviewed GO pattern expectations for biosynthetic/regulation terms and avoided adding new over-specified axioms\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: chemical-entity guidance applied; pH 7.3 CHEBI term retained in logical definition\n+- [x] EDITS: used `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: logical relationships preserved appropriately\n+- [x] METADATA: corrected `created_by`; did not add new-term metadata to existing terms\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: existing PMID retained; no new references introduced\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_CO